metadata.name: The Fall of Icarus
metadata.description:
Go to the Louvre museum in Paris and look up. There you may discover 'The Fall of Icarus' by Merry-Joseph Blondel.

In this animated re-imagining of the work, the art is brought to life from a digital image captured at the Louvre museum, and we find Icarus tumbling down from a swirling sky.

The initial NFT collector will receive this 12 second video, as well as the opportunity to have a longer 60 second version.
